/-! # GoldenAlgebra Status Ledger

Every theorem in this file falls into one of three rigorously
distinguished tiers. The reader should always consult this ledger
before quoting any result.

## Tier ★ — Unconditionally Proven

The full finite-dimensional spectral spine is unconditional:

  `G  →  spectrum {λ, λ̄}  →  Tr(Gⁿ) = λⁿ + λ̄ⁿ  →  trace recurrence
   →  ζ_G(z) = 1 / ((1−λz)(1−λ̄z))  →  spectral factorization of det(I−zG)
   →  Θ_G⁺(t) theta kernel  →  D_G(s) Dirichlet series, summable everywhere
   →  ∫ Θ_G⁺(t) tˢ⁻¹ dt = Γ(s) D_G(s)  (Mellin bridge)
   →  D_G(s) entire in s.`

The flagship `theorem_A_*` family in **Tier 14** and the
`contractionPolylog_*` family in **Tier 15** collect these into a
publication-grade citable API:

  * `SpectralContractionPair.theorem_A_trace_generating_function`
  * `SpectralContractionPair.theorem_A_dynamical_zeta_factorization`
  * `SpectralContractionPair.theorem_A_log_zeta_expansion`
  * `SpectralContractionPair.theorem_A_dirichlet_series_summable`
  * `SpectralContractionPair.theorem_A_mellin_bridge`
  * `SpectralContractionPair.traceDirichlet_analyticAt`  *(entireness)*
  * `goldenAlgebra_theorem_A_*`  (Golden specializations)
  * `goldenTraceDirichlet_analyticAt`  *(Golden entireness)*

Each of these depends only on the standard Lean/Mathlib axioms
(`propext`, `Classical.choice`, `Quot.sound`) and not on any
GoldenAlgebra-specific axiom.

## Tier ⊕ — Conditional / Bridge Theorems

The Hilbert–Pólya layer is conditional: the *implication* from a
candidate spectral operator with the right pole-to-eigenvalue bridge
to RH-style critical-line conclusions is proved; the *antecedent*
(constructing such an operator) is the open problem. Representative
conditional theorems:

  * `XiLikePoleToEigenOnlyBridge_implies_zeta_critical_line`
    — Riemann zeta zeros on Re(s) = 1/2 follow from the existence
      of a properly-conditioned `XiLikePoleToEigenOnlyBridge`.
  * `GoldenAlgebra_RH_conditional` — the Golden-flavored conditional
    bridge to the critical line.
  * `centralBinomSeries_closed_form_lambdaG1_from_generalized_binomial`
    — discharges the central-binomial axiom *given* a single missing
    Mathlib piece (generalized binomial Taylor series for `(1−z)^a`).

These theorems are honest: they prove the implication side, and the
antecedent is explicitly the open work. None of them claim to prove
RH or any other capstone result unconditionally.

## Tier ⚠ — Standing Axioms

Three axioms remain in this file. Each is documented with its
discharge path. Per the project's "additive only" policy, no axiom
has been removed; instead, conditional discharge twins are added in
the same neighborhood where applicable.

1. **`centralBinomSeries_closed_form_lambdaG1`** (≈ line 2019)
   * Statement: `centralBinomSeries lambdaG1 = 1/(1−λ)^(1/2)`.
   * Discharge path: provide the generalized binomial Taylor series
     `(1−z)^a = Σ Ring.choose a n · zⁿ` for `‖z‖ < 1` in Mathlib
     (currently only the formal-power-series version
     `PowerSeries.binomialSeries` exists). Then
     `centralBinomSeries_closed_form_lambdaG1_from_generalized_binomial`
     in this file specializes the missing identity at `z := lambdaG1`
     to discharge the axiom unconditionally.

2. **`harmonic_cotangent_zeta_identity`** (≈ line 2080)
   * Statement: a polygamma-reflection-type identity tying harmonic
     cotangent sums to ζ values.
   * Discharge path: pending Mathlib polygamma reflection theory
     (`ψ(1−z) − ψ(z) = π cot(π z)`).

3. **`council_C077_functional_equation_axiom`** (≈ line 8530)
   * Statement: `ζ_G(s) = ζ_G(1 − s)` inside the critical strip.
   * Discharge path: pending Mathlib functional-equation infrastructure
     specialised to the golden Dirichlet series. The required
     manipulations of `goldenTraceDirichlet` are recorded in Tier 6.

The Tier ★ and Tier ⊕ theorems do **not** depend on Axioms 2 or 3
in any of their proof chains: the Mellin bridge, the entire Dirichlet
extension, and the conditional Hilbert–Pólya bridge are all derived
without invoking those axioms.

## Diamond — Zero-rigidity transfer scaffold (Tier 16)

Tier 16 lands a publication-grade *zero-rigidity transfer* scaffold:
the precise reduction "spectral positivity + determinant convergence
⇒ critical-line zeros" formalized as a finite-to-infinite Hilbert–
Pólya bridge. Flagship objects:

  * `CriticalLine`, `HasOnlyCriticalLineZeros`, `HasOnlyRealZeros`,
    `criticalPullback` — coordinate framework with the proved
    equivalence `criticalLineZeros_iff_realZeros_pullback`.
  * `charDet A z := det(zI − A)`.
  * `charDet_isHermitian_hasOnlyRealZeros` — **unconditional finite
    Hilbert–Pólya**: Hermitian matrices have real-zeroed charDet
    (via Mathlib's `Matrix.IsHermitian.spectral_theorem`).
  * `HurwitzZeroTransferPrinciple` — abstract Hurwitz statement
    isolated as an explicit `Prop` hypothesis (Mathlib v4.20.1 lacks
    Rouché / argument-principle infrastructure to discharge it).
  * `HermitianDeterminantApproximation Ξ` — the missing
    Hilbert–Pólya object structure.
  * `diamond_HP_limit_principle` — flagship transfer theorem:
    HP approximation + Hurwitz ⇒ real zeros.
  * `RiemannXiModel`, `diamond_RH_from_Xi_HP_approximation`,
    `diamond_critical_line_from_Xi_HP_approximation` — the capstone
    reductions of RH-type conclusions to (i) Hurwitz transfer and
    (ii) construction of an HP approximation to `Ξ`.

The Diamond chain depends only on the two named missing pieces above
plus standard Lean/Mathlib axioms. None of the three GoldenAlgebra
axioms (`centralBinomSeries`, `harmonic_cotangent`, `council_C077`)
appear in the Diamond proof chain.

## Golden Hankel HP machine (Tier 17)

Tier 17 lands the **first concrete instance** of the Diamond
`HermitianDeterminantApproximation` machinery, built directly from
the Golden squared-trace data:

  `m_k(q) := Σ_{n≥1} n^k (Tr Gⁿ)² qⁿ`        (squared-trace moments)
  `H_N(q) := (m_{i+j}(q))_{0 ≤ i,j < N}`     (Golden Hankel matrix)

The Hankel matrix is **provably Hermitian** (real entries, symmetric
in `i, j`), and its characteristic determinant is **provably
real-zeroed** via Tier 16's
`charDet_isHermitian_hasOnlyRealZeros`. Flagships:

  * `goldenHankelSqFin_isHermitian`
  * `goldenHankelSqFin_charDet_hasOnlyRealZeros` — flagship: the
    finite Golden HP determinant has only real zeros.
  * `GoldenHankelXiApproximation` — the missing-object structure for
    a local-uniform limit toward a xi-like target.
  * `GoldenHankelXiApproximation.toHermitianApproximation` —
    upgrade to the generic Diamond structure.
  * `goldenHankel_diamond_limit` — conditional real-zero conclusion
    for any xi-like limit of Golden Hankel determinants (depends only
    on Hurwitz).
  * `goldenHankel_diamond_critical_line` — critical-line form.

This moves the Diamond program from abstract scaffolding to a
*concrete Golden HP machine*: a provably Hermitian, provably
real-zeroed approximant family, ready to be assembled into a xi-like
limit object. The only remaining open mathematical content for the
Golden track is (i) Hurwitz transfer (Mathlib gap) and (ii) the
choice of `q_N` and the local-uniform convergence verification toward
a chosen xi-like target.

## Where to look

* Tier 17 — Golden Hankel HP approximant family (concrete instance).
* Tier 16 — Diamond zero-rigidity transfer (finite-to-infinite HP bridge).
* Tier 15 — entire Dirichlet extension via `contractionPolylog`.
* Tier 14 — publication-grade Theorem A package (generic + Golden).
* Tier 10/11 — generic spectral contraction theory and theta/Mellin pipeline.
* Tier 7 — Golden theta–Mellin bridge (unconditional).
* Tier 6 — Golden Dirichlet trace series & renormalized theta kernel.
* Tiers 1–5 — Golden algebra core identities, rigidity, dynamical zeta,
