-- Uₙ has cost exactly 5/6; total clearing Dₙ³·Uₙ costs 3 + 5/6 = 23/6
-- ≈ 3.833 — PROVED below the tiny-mode threshold 3.9113. This is the
-- first denominator skeleton genuinely in the winning range.

/-- **PROVED — the exact top-layer total cost.** `3 + 5/6 = 23/6`. -/
theorem topLayer_total_cost_eq : (3 : ℝ) + 5 / 6 = 23 / 6 := by norm_num

/--
**PROVED — the top-layer denominator skeleton WINS the race.**
`3 + 5/6 = 23/6 ≈ 3.833` is strictly below the tiny-mode threshold
`−log|λ₃| ≈ 3.9113`. The total clearing `Dₙ³·Uₙ` beats the tiny-mode
decay `|λ₃|ⁿ` — the first skeleton genuinely in the winning range.
