-- === Phase LXIII: External ζ(3) Elimination via Apéry Approximants ===
-- The symmetric pole-6 kernel produces
--   L_n = q_n^{(5)}·ζ(5) + q_n^{(3)}·ζ(3) − p_n.
-- Externally eliminate ζ(3) using Apéry's ζ(3) approximants
--   A_m = q_m·ζ(3) − p_m
-- via the algebraic combination
--   q_m·L_n − q_n^{(3)}·A_m = (q_m·q_n^{(5)})·ζ(5) − (q_m·p_n − q_n^{(3)}·p_m),
-- a pure ζ(5) form. Algebraically PROVED below. The race STILL loses
-- (best margin ≈ −0.471 at b=2, n=6, m=10) — but only mildly, not
-- catastrophically. External elimination remains too expensive because
-- Apéry approximants do not target the π²/3 curvature coupling.

/-- **PROVED — the external-elimination algebraic identity.** Given a
symmetric form `L_n = q5·ζ5 + q3·ζ3 − p_n` and an Apéry-style ζ(3)
approximant `A_m = q_m·ζ3 − p_m`, the combination
`q_m·L_n − q3·A_m` is a pure ζ(5) linear form
`(q_m·q5)·ζ5 − (q_m·p_n − q3·p_m)`. -/
theorem external_elimination_identity
    (q3 q5 pn qm pm zeta3 zeta5 : ℝ) :
    qm * (q5 * zeta5 + q3 * zeta3 - pn) - q3 * (qm * zeta3 - pm)
      = qm * q5 * zeta5 - (qm * pn - q3 * pm) := by
  ring

