/--
The **rational-sum / arithmetic-obstruction diagnosis**:
PROVED:
  • Algebraic identity `1/(n^5·(1−(ρ/n)^N)) = (2n)^N/(n^5·((2n)^N−1))`
    at ρ = 1/2.
  • Concrete first-term values (N=1, N=2).
  • Denominator factor `(2n)^N − 1` grows fast (specific values
