-- === Phase LXXXI: The R_a Hierarchy Lesson — Triangularity, Step a, Highly Composite ===
-- Combining several R_a's is TRIANGULAR — to kill channels ζ(6)..ζ(m+4)
-- while keeping ζ(5), one simply selects the largest step R_m. So
-- combining R_1, …, R_m gives nothing new beyond R_m itself.
-- The R_a family IS the hierarchy:
--   R_2: ζ(5), ζ(7),  ζ(9),  ζ(11), …
--   R_3: ζ(5), ζ(8),  ζ(11), ζ(14), …
--   R_4: ζ(5), ζ(9),  ζ(13), ζ(17), …
--   R_5: ζ(5), ζ(10), ζ(15), ζ(20), …
--   R_6: ζ(5), ζ(11), ζ(17), ζ(23), …
