R_a summand.** For `a | N` (with `N = a·k` and `x = 2n`):
`(x^N)/(x^N − 1) · (x^N − 1)/(x^a − 1) · x^{−(N−a)} = x^a/(x^a − 1)`.
This is the precise statement of "highly-composite N + a|N reproduces
the R_a residual ladder." Carried as a named target because the proof
needs the auxiliary hypothesis `x^N ≠ 1`, which can fail for special
roots of unity. -/
