/--
**Named record — the SIX RULES of Overflow Analysis.**
  Rule 1: Body selection (B ∼ A or A − B = O(1)).
  Rule 2: Peeling (O_B[A] = A − B or A/B).
  Rule 3: Residue (lim of peeled object).
  Rule 4: Tower extraction (iterate).
  Rule 5: Constants as residues.
  Rule 6: Corrections remember discreteness.
-/
structure OverflowAnalysisRules where
  rule1_body_selection : Prop
  rule2_peeling : Prop
