/-! # Tier 85 — Naive Conjugacy Cannot Be the Hilbert–Pólya Transform

Step 197 records the *crucial caveat*: naive unitary conjugacy
`H_HP = U · H_log · U⁻¹` is too strong, because it preserves the
`log n` spectrum — the wrong spectrum for the Hilbert–Pólya operator.
This tier proves that caveat **unconditionally**.

Conjugation by a unit preserves the spectrum exactly
(`spectrum.units_conjugate`).  Hence any transform realized as naive
conjugacy of the arithmetic log Hamiltonian cannot change the spectrum;
and since the Hilbert–Pólya operator must carry the zeta-zero spectrum
— which differs from the arithmetic `log n` spectrum — no naive
conjugacy of `H_log` can be the HP operator.  This is exactly why
Step 197's transform must be the *regularized / distributional* one.

Items 34-35 of the operator program. Tier ★ — Unconditionally Proven:
both proofs depend only on the standard Lean/Mathlib axioms. -/

section NaiveConjugacy

variable {R A : Type*} [CommSemiring R] [Ring A] [Algebra R A]

/-- **Naive unitary conjugacy preserves the log spectrum** (item 34,
`naive_unitary_conjugacy_preserves_log_spectrum`).  If the candidate
Hilbert–Pólya operator `H_HP` is produced from the arithmetic log
Hamiltonian `H_log` by naive conjugacy `H_HP = U · H_log · U⁻¹`, then
`H_HP` has *exactly* the spectrum of `H_log`.  Genuine consequence of
`spectrum.units_conjugate`. -/
theorem naive_unitary_conjugacy_preserves_log_spectrum
    (H_log H_HP : A) (U : Aˣ) (hconj : H_HP = U * H_log * U⁻¹) :
    spectrum R H_HP = spectrum R H_log := by
  rw [hconj]; exact spectrum.units_conjugate

/-- **Naive conjugacy is rejected for the Hilbert–Pólya target**
(item 35, `naive_unitary_conjugacy_rejected_for_HP_target`).  The HP
operator must carry the zeta-zero spectrum, which differs from the
arithmetic `log n` spectrum.  Hence, whenever `spectrum R H_HP` differs
from `spectrum R H_log` (the defining HP requirement), `H_HP` is
provably *not* any naive conjugate of `H_log` — the dual transform must
be genuinely non-naive. -/
theorem naive_unitary_conjugacy_rejected_for_HP_target
    (H_log H_HP : A)
    (hHP : spectrum R H_HP ≠ spectrum R H_log) :
    ¬ ∃ U : Aˣ, H_HP = U * H_log * U⁻¹ := by
  rintro ⟨U, hconj⟩
  exact hHP (naive_unitary_conjugacy_preserves_log_spectrum H_log H_HP U hconj)

end NaiveConjugacy

