`ρ_D = ρ_m`           : mass-as-desire identification (`IsMassEqualsDesire`)
`Δ Φ = 4πG ρ_D`       : Poisson sourcing (`IsDesirePotential`)
`q̈ = − ∇ Φ`           : Newtonian motion (`IsCollapseTrajectory`)
`u'' + u = A + Bu + Cu² + Du³` :  compression polynomial gravity (Tier 92)
`ẋ = (J − M) ∇ E`     : master operator (Tier 94)
`E_unit = E_collapse + E_edge + E_area`  : unit-lattice frustration (Tier 95)
`K ψ = λ ψ`           : Hessian eigenmode (`HessianEigenpair`)
`u(t) = Σ aₖ cos(k ω t)` : sparse pair-compression Fourier ansatz
                          (`FourierCompressionAnsatz`)
